article.headline: Dayton 75, Fordham 56
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Sean Finn scored 13 points on 6-for-6 shooting and led four scorers in double figures in Dayton's 75-56 victory over Fordham on Saturday. Keith Waleskowski added 12 points for the Flyers (14-3, 4-0 Atlantic 10), who won their fourth straight. Monty Scott scored 11 points on 5-for-5 shooting, and Warren Williams shot 3-for-3 from 3-point range and finished with 10 points. Derrick Breland hit four 3-pointers for 12 points, and Mushon Ya'akoski added 11 points for Fordham (4-11, 1-3). Dayton, which held a 33-22 lead at halftime, shot 28-for-44 (63.6 percent) and outrebounded the Rams 41-14. After Waleskowskis tip-in gave Dayton a 6-5 lead at 16:03 of the first half, the Rams went on a 10-4 run and took a 15-10 lead at 9:32. Jarrell-Wright scored seven points in the outburst. Michael Haynes' three-point play tied the score at 21, and Dayton scored 12 straight points to take a 33-21 lead in the final seconds of the first half. The Flyers outscored Fordham 21-7 in the final 9:32 of the half. Dayton went on an 18-4 run at the start of the second half to open up a 51-30 lead.
